  "20-1": (
    caption: [Assimilation of CO2 into biomass in plants. The light-driven synthesis of ATP and NADPH, described in Chapter 19, provides energy and reducing power for the fixation of CO2 into trioses, from which all the carbon-containing compounds of the plant cell are synthesized. The processes shown with red arrows are the focus of this chapter.],
