    caption: [Role of the Pi–triose phosphate antiporter in the trans- port of ATP and reducing equivalents. Dihydroxyacetone phosphate leaves the chloroplast and is converted to glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate in the cytosol. The cytosolic glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate dehydrogenase],
