  "20-17": (
    caption: [Source of ATP and NADPH. ATP and NADPH p roduced by the light reactions are essential substrates for the reduction of CO2. The photosynthetic reactions that produce ATP and NADPH are accompanied by movement of protons (red) from the stroma into the thylakoid, creating alkaline conditions in the stroma. Magnesium ions pass from the thylakoid into the stroma, increasing the stromal \[Mg21\].],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
